{
  "title": "WebStorageStore",
  "description": "KeyValueStore over the Web Storage API (`localStorage` or `sessionStorage`). Web Storage holds only strings, so values are JSON-serialized on write and parsed on read — they must be JSON-serializable (**no** Blobs/`ArrayBuffer`s; use IndexedDbKeyValueStore for those). The backend is synchronous with a small (~5–10 MB) quota; the async interface wraps it so call sites stay uniform across stores. This is the moral successor of the former `JsonStore`: JSON is intrinsic here because the backend can only hold strings.",
